reviews.review: Far stronger than "The Last Jedi", I was left feeling that the trilogy would have worked better had J.J. Abrams had directed all three films. This was fittingly by far the most epic of all Star Wars films. The characters continued to evolve, their motivations were believable, the plot thickened, and Luke even admits he was wrong. Some new characters were duds (the new droid D-0), but luckily there were so many strong and beloved characters that it didn't matter. I saw it in IMAX 3D and will try to see it at least once again before it leaves theaters.
This movie gave me TESB vibes. The pacing is really good, there wasn't any boring parts in the movie, it had great character arcs, and it was a blast! I can't believe people don't like this movie.
